article.headline: Princeton 63, Columbia 35
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Zach Finley came off the bench to score 11 points and pull down eight rebounds as Princeton beat Columbia 63-35 on Saturday night. Kareem Maddox added nine points and five boards for the Tigers (9-8, 4-0 Ivy League), while Dan Mavraides and Kareem Maddox finished with eight points each. Zack Crimmins had five points to lead the Lions (8-12, 3-3), who missed their first 14 shots and only hit 23.9 percent from the field. Princeton was in command throughout, jumping out to a 9-0 lead and taking a 27-11 lead at the break. The Tigers then maintained double-digit leads throughout the second half, leading by as many as 30 points. Princeton also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding Columbia 41-26.
